Iranian students are ready to die for their country’s nuclear program.
Created a living shield
Several hundred college students have created a living shield around a nuclear facility in Iran.
With their gesture, they want to express their support for their country’s nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
On Tuesday afternoon, the students prayed in front of the building and then called for the death of the United States and Israel.
On Tuesday, several hundred university students in Isfahan, Iran, created a living shield around the Isfahan Nuclear Technology Center, where uranium is processed.
They show that they are ready to defend their country’s nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) said in a recent report that Iran appears to have not stopped pursuing a nuclear weapon.
A possible attack on Iran’s nuclear facilities is being discussed in Israel.
At noon, before entering the Isfahan nuclear facility, the students prayed and then called for the death of America and Israel.
In the event of an attack aimed at crippling Iran’s nuclear program as much as possible, the Israeli press said the target, in addition to the Isfahan center, would be a facility in Natanz where uranium is enriched.
The menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight, with 9 percent of schoolchildren being overweight and 5 percent of children being obese.
Obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles, according to a recent survey.
It shows again how important the environment in which a person grows up and the patterns in which he is surrounded are for healthy development.
On tables in obese children, for example, sausages appear up to half as often as in families of children with normal weight.
Fry fries had by dinner the day before the research associated with an awareness event called Obesity is not a coincidence for more than 19 percent of the obese.
In families of fat people, it is also not customary to play sports, but this applies to most families of today's schoolchildren - only 15 percent of children answered that their parents find time for active movement at least once a week.
A survey of 900 children
The survey took place at the end of last school year and was attended by almost 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was the second year of the event Obesity is not a coincidence, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from the 4th to 8th grades have participated in the project.
Proper nutrition and plenty of exercise in the family is one of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of children who are overweight or even obese.
“Only half of those surveyed, for example, reported eating five breakfast-breakfast-lunch-breakfast-dinner meals a day, which is one of the basic preconditions for proper nutrition,” one of the survey’s findings said.
No breakfast and evening sausage
Experts point out that for healthy development, relative details, such as regular family breakfast time, are also important.
In the Czech Republic, only 23 percent of schoolchildren have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst part was finding out that in a dozen households there is no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are much more often consumed.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed regularly play sports, the result for their parents was less than half - 15 percent.
Build your own diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to make their own diet according to their own taste and opinion.
"The dietary preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
"The high popularity of sweet lemonades is particularly alarming," the study said in its final report.
For lunch, pasta just above poultry won the main meal.
But the children practically did not want legumes at all, and the popularity of fish and midday vegetable dishes is also low.
Inclination to health
At the same time, the survey showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the end of the awareness lecture, obesity is not a coincidence, in many cases there was a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition," the project said.
For example, sweet lemonades were marked by the fact that more children would prefer plain water.
Children were also more likely to check poultry and fish as the main meal of the day and limit sweet foods and dumplings.
A stylist must also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the introductory article about the way stylists learn, I complained so little that there was a lot already in the introductory lessons.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three professionals in the field, dressing problematic characters and a seminar on how it works on the stage.
And it's gonna get worse.
The closer to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
And even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is really "stuck".
This time, Director Alenka and I discussed (there is not a single boy in the course) how to dress a woman who does not have a perfectly symmetrical figure.
And that's the vast majority.
Someone has a short neck, someone has a boyish figure without proper curves, and someone is overweight.
A stylist must know how to visually soften wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or add the necessary curves.
We got tips on how a woman like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. bigger breasts and hips and a narrow waist, to emphasize the figure nicely and at the same time not to dress the woman too challengingly.
For example, if the difference between the waist and hips is such that the skirt or pants really do not fit, then it is worth to have at least one such piece tailored to you.
You will definitely not regret it, because perfectly fitting clothes are unbeatable.
In a skirt tailored to you you will feel much better than in one that constantly shifts, leans out, lags behind in the waist and the like.
The boy's character can afford to wear clothes with trimming, applications, embroidery or picking.
Of course, there are many such information and types of characters, so I am glad that I have a whole week to sort out all the information in my head.
And I'm still afraid that given the homework I've been assigned, there's a lot going on.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity to invent two outfits: daytime and evening.
We must take into account the current appearance, the fashionable style of a given personality and the type of character.
I'll "dress" Miranda Kerr, you may know her from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
I am happy in spirit, for me personally definitely better than Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently gained about a hundred kilos (please take into account the exaggeration), or young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut clothes from magazines or search the Internet and print and then graphically process them.
Moodboard, as the whole result is called, then expresses our personal style and relationship to graphic representation.
Thinking about the graphic aspect of styling is also important.
The stylist does not only dress physically, but also creates, for example, so-called product pages in magazines (for specific purposes, for example, trendy handbags, coats, etc.).
Stylist and designer Mario Kamen<0xC3><0xAD>k told us about it.
But not until Sunday.
A stylist must have a general overview
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about the types of characters, was enriched by three guests from the industry.
Stylist Honza The humble, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
James reminded us that fashion is an illusion and a stylist should be able to use it.
And a handy stylist can work with one piece of clothing in different ways.
Variability is key in this case.
So, for example, such a trenchcoat (or if you originally want a trenchcoat) can be worn classically over jeans and a T-shirt as a coat, but you can also wear it on a bare body, put on boats and take pictures as a dress.
Or just roll up your sleeves or collars and immediately the whole look looks different.
"Play with it," he said.
But what I appreciated most was the following advice: "You need to know the rules perfectly for work."
"Then you can start breaking them," said Jakub.
Finally, it is clear to me why we are crushing all the lessons, what to combine with, what to do, why, even if we sometimes see something different in fashion magazines.
Not to mention the parades.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that the stylist must have much more clothes ready than they can take.
So for a fashion story that will have ten pages (i.e. ten outfits), I have to be ready to "set" at least fifteen.
And also that in the photo of clothes looks and works in combination with other pieces sometimes completely different than in reality.
This is something that we need to take into account when creating an outfit.
The fact that image and style sometimes make up half of the success was confirmed by Honza Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly a miraculous singer, but her image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the approach to using the services of stylists is rather cold.
Even familiar faces sometimes consider it useless (it is enough that I know something, the way I look at it is secondary).
And if someone lets us create styling, then we have to count on the fact that he will most likely dictate to us a completely different (smaller) size than he really has.
Then you have to google and see if the boulevard hasn’t written about the fact that the celebrity has lost weight and the like.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario put it on our hearts that it is not enough for a stylist to orient himself in fashion and be able to assemble an outfit.
In his work, he primarily communicates with the people he dresses, and so it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to estimate people, not to be incited, to stand for your opinion.
"If you're ordered by a manager to sort out her wardrobe and add nice pieces to it, you can't throw away the whole closet and say, for God's sake, that's terrible."
"Find at least a few things you'll praise and recommend what they can be worn for," Mario says.
He also specifically showed us what everything must contain the so-called "place bag", or bag for the place.
It's the one you put around your waist and you have all the necessary propriety with you.
In addition to bright things such as scissors, hair roller or closing pins, there is also a nylon thread (with which the stylist helps to take pictures of products such as handbags or hats), special clips that will clamp clothes at the back, if it is larger (a pin or other clamp would not be allowed), a pin or a pin.
In order not only to listen, but also to try something practically, we learned how to properly water shoes.
Even when photographing in the studio, where there is a flat surface, the sole could be damaged, let alone outside.
And so we glued and glued.
We should not even touch the shoes with the scissors, so that they do not accidentally get damaged.
It really needs skill.
Mario pleased me when he praised my creation without reservation.
This skill is not really my friend.
This is only a small fraction of what we heard about the second weekend of the course.
It is becoming increasingly clear to me that doing styling on a professional level is really not a walk in the pink orchard, no matter who says what they want.
Need for Speed: The Run is an American racing game.
Testimonials
Originally a carefree ride, due to a series of completely unnecessary sloppy mistakes, it turns into a routine morning trip to a shift.
Although the ambition was largely fulfilled, it is not worth it if no one obviously wanted to do anything more.
The new episode with the subtitle The Run aroused high expectations before the release.
He promised that the old Need for Speed racing series would once again move a bit in a new direction and from playable demos it seemed like a game that would not have to be just a number in the genre of action racing.
We were also curious how the inserted passages would turn out, in which the protagonist would get out of the car and run on his own.
But as with the NFS series, many things are a little different than we expected.
These are potentially decent arcade races, but the whole drags down a few unnecessary mistakes that have been appearing in the series for several years.
So these are not even mistakes, but rather a manifestation of some incomprehensible laziness of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced to a story whose main character Jack has certain personal problems and as a solution is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You drive on the west coast of San Francisco and your task is to arrive first in New York.
The idea carries with it several interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages, and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race is driven on a different track and the stages are set in different, sufficiently different and interesting environments.
You don’t feel like the game offers the same thing all the time.
In addition, some of the environments are very nice to see, although the technical level of graphics corresponds to the previous parts of the series.
So it's nothing world-class.
But driving through the desert, autumn landscape or high in the snowy mountains looks visually very pleasant.
In addition, the races are from time to time diversified by some atypical element.
In the desert, for example, you will wind up in a sandstorm, which significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains, you have to be careful not to be overwhelmed by an avalanche.
In addition, the individual races are quite well placed after each other.
There are only a few types, but that’s enough.
For a while you try to overtake the required number of opponents (essentially a classic race), then you catch up with time (classic fight with stopwatches), and then you will be waiting for a duel with a single opponent.
From time to time, even the police will get involved in this, which makes all your efforts even more unpleasant.
The novelty is the passages outside the car.
It’s more of an interactive animation where Jack usually runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right moments.
It's not complicated.
Surprisingly, however, there are far fewer of these passages in the game than you would expect (in particular, perhaps only three).
In the end, however, it is to the benefit of the matter, because this element has no chance of becoming annoying and in the context of the above, it is thus among the elements that diversify the game.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
This means that it is definitely not something nowadays, but it can not be said that it would be a negative.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you will have to look elsewhere.
But the more action-packed racing, the local driving model still fits quite well, even though we could find a better one in the competition.
So far, everything is in perfect order.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the model is no longer colliding.
From a game of this type we do not expect it to calculate complex deformations and collisions, but if before virtually any impact on any object you do not have the slightest idea how your car will behave, then probably not everything is in order.
Typically, when overtaking or passing cars in normal operation, sometimes you just lick each other slightly, but other times in an almost identical situation, your car ends up in wild pirouettes.
Or even straight forward.
Thanks to the restart system, it does not matter much, but it will reliably defuse you.
Restarts are solved so that if you break or go far off the track, the game will throw you back to the last catch point on the track.
There are only five reboots available in each race.
When you run out of them, you have to start the race again.
Therefore, it is more of a help in case something does not work, than if you can rely on them explicitly.
But sometimes even restarts do not help, they will be solved only by the need to learn a given section of the race by heart.
The big disadvantage of the game is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some corners, for example, need to pass in a specific way, otherwise you simply will not fit into them.
Other times you will meet "civil" cars in the same configuration at a given place, whether you arrive there first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially true in situations where you can see an opponent passing easily between two opposing cars in front of you, while when you get there, the cars are already in such a position that you have to bypass or brake them.
It does not matter when you reach them, because it is "counted" so that the situation always occurs just before your nose.
The opponents have another advantage.
During the whole game you will encounter several places where, again regardless of the time, you will always be overtaken by the same opponent at the same place.
Most of all, it beats at the end of the game on a long bridge, where you drive in the opposite direction.
The opponent must get there before you, perhaps at any cost.
When it drives in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the opposite cars, so at first you get a lot of smashing.
You can understand the intention to make the game more exciting and adrenaline-filled, but the execution is so obvious that it will reliably disgust you quickly.
And it's a shame, because despite the simple driving model, playing is fun and sometimes action-packed enough that sometimes you literally can't keep track of what's flying.
And it doesn’t really matter if it’s a concept with 50 unique tracks, sorting races so that boredom doesn’t have a chance, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to watch out for petrol pumps on the road, because that’s where you can change the car, even though in the vast majority of cases you can do with what you just have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sportsmen are suitable for urban areas, strong American storms on straight highways and exotic supersports for technical riding, for example, on winding mountain roads.
With the main story mode goes hand in hand with the challenge mode, which are races in individual locations that you know from the story.
Here you get not only medals, but also experience points to your profile, which is common to the challenges and the story.
To get a higher level of the driver, various items are unlocked: starting with cars and ending with backgrounds for the profile.
At the same time, it is again connected to the online Autolog function, which compares your results with other players and provides other community functions.
One of the other difficult to understand is the situation from the last race in the story.
With your car you will get to the subway tunnel (be it), where you drive it in the dark on the tracks (be it).
The tachometer flashes the numbers between 150 and 200 km/h (albeit) and in this the metro set arrives from behind and uncompromisingly scrapes you.
In the editorial office, we will probably have a few more days of discussion about whether no one really thought a bit when creating the game, or whether the authors consider us to be really such a fool.
The technical side of the game is nothing special, but at least the overall visual impression is in most cases very pleasant and in some cases even great.
It freezes in such a way that at some of the more tense moments the shooting decreases, and in some cases quite tragically.
But this applies especially to storms with a larger number of participants, when smooth shooting would no longer be useful to you anyway.
The sound page is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to please the widest possible range of rather younger audiences, a soundtrack from the category "every dog is a different village" was created, but it can be assumed that because of listening to music, someone will probably not buy the game.
Need for Speed: The Run: Need for Speed: The Run
If the game were to avoid completely unnecessary errors, then we would not be afraid to say that The Run is the best work of the NFS for the last few years.
This is how the game works unfinished.
It’s definitely fun, but be prepared for mistakes that will blow your eyes with the power of airport spotlights.
