Along with a decline in economic activity and an increase in unemployment, foreign direct investment fell sharply in the last 10 years. According to the Ministry of Finance, between January and June, foreign direct investment amounted to $630,697, representing a decrease of 87.74% compared to $5,143,312 for the same period in the previous year.
