The meeting of the two presidents in the city of Guadalajara will serve to exchange information on political issues between the two countries,” the Uruguayan presidential office said on its website.
According to local media, Mujica will try to get Calder<0xC3><0xB3>n to support Uruguay in the dispute with France, which occurred when French President Nicolas Sarkozy placed the South American country on the tax haven list at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
