The recovery can be partially explained by the purchase of machines that are necessary for the restoration of areas destroyed by the earthquake and subsequent tsunami.
Businesses increased their investments by 1.1%, spending drops by 0.9% from January to March. This is the first decline after six months of continuous growth.
However, the real awakening of the Japanese economy is based solely on the impulse that forces us to use the crisis to get out of it, or to restore infrastructure, to use the scarcity to start completely from scratch.
Japan has awakened, in particular due to the development of domestic consumption, which currently accounts for 60% of Japan's GDP.
This variable increased by 1%, thanks to an increase in spending on vehicles, travel and leisure activities.
